    • Method Detail

      • importShipment

        org.w3c.dom.Document importShipment(YFSEnvironment env,
                                    org.w3c.dom.Document inXML)
                             throws com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException,
                                    java.rmi.RemoteException

        importShipment will import a shipment, already processed to some extent in an external system, into the Sterling system.

        The imported Shipments should only be for orders that are already in the Sterling system if OrderAvailableOnSystem flag on the Shipment is Y.

        Related Documents
        Input XML Input DTD Output XML Output DTD Error XML Error DTD

        User Exits: None

        Events Raised:
        Raised during the transaction IMPORT_SHIPMENT.

          ON_SUCCESS:
            This event is raised upon successful execution of importShipment.
            Data published - YDM_IMPORT_SHIPMENT.ON_SUCCESS.xml
            Key data - shipment_dbd.txt
              Template Support: Yes

        Audits: None

        Pre Conditions:
        The imported Shipments should only be for orders that are already in the Sterling system if OrderAvailableOnSystem is Y.

        Post Conditions: None

        Output Template Support: Yes

        Database Extensibility Support: Yes


        Additional Information:

        Please maintain the sequence of the Elements in the input XML.

        In the yfs_shipment or yfs_shipment_h record, HAS_OTHER_SHIPMENTS will be set to N;
        SHIPMENT_CLOSED_FLAG set to Y;
        SHIPMENT_CONFIRM_UPDATES_DONE set to Y;
        SHIPMENT_CONTAINERIZED_FLAG set to Y if container elements present in put, else set to N;
        SHIPMENT_DELIVER_UPDATES_DONE set to Y;
        SHIPMENT_PLANNED_FLAG set to N.

        InstructionType is defaulted to OTHER if not passed in the input xml.

        In yfs_shipment_container or yfs_shipment_container_h record , HAS_OTHER_CONTAINERS is set to N.

        Table Keys ( = Primary Keys like ShipmentKey), if not passed, will be generated.

        Parameters:
        env - Required. Environment handle returned by the createEnvironment API.
        inXML - Required. For more information, see the associated input xml files.

        Returns:
        An XML document that contains details of the imported shipment. For details on the output, refer to the associated output files.

        Throws:
        com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException - Exception containing error codes in the standard error files.
        java.rmi.RemoteException - Java's default remote exception handler.
